OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Ron Hendrey
OL,5,F"And that was the only time I ever
OL,6,Fknew the gun to blister, because we
OL,7,Fwere firing nonstop for about 15
OL,8,Fminutes. And the barrel gets hot. They
OL,9,Fwill only stand so much heat.
OL,11,F"The landing craft were on the way
OL,12,Fbefore we finished firing. It was very
OL,13,Fwell organised.
OL,15,F"In point of fact we didn't really
OL,16,Fknow what we were firing at. All we
OL,17,Fwere given was a range and we had to
OL,18,Fhit it. When we fired a shell we
OL,19,Fdidn't know where it was going to
OL,20,Fland. Were we killing innocent French
OL,21,Fpeople? We don't know.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/7
